<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Provides Loan to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Saudi Fund for
Development has agreed to provide an additional loan of 10.5
million U.S. dollars for Nepal's Bagmati Irrigation Project,
Nepal's official RSS news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With this new loan, the total Saudi Arabia fund for the project
 amounts to 36.8 million dollars, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the project will irrigate an area of 37,000
hectares when completed in December 1998, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
