<HEADLINE> Turkey, Israel, US to Hold Maneuvers on January 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Turkey announced today that it
will hold joint exercises code-named "Reliant Mermaid" with Israel
and the United States in the international waters near Israeli
coast on January 7, the Anatolia news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a statement issued by the U.S. Embassy in Ankara
said the naval and air joint exercises are aimed at improving the
abilities of search and rescue of the three naval forces.
</P>
<P>
It said that the joint exercises will also test the the naval
forces' reciprocation capability in the Mediterranean Sea.
</P>
<P>
The planned maneuvers, which have been postponed for several
times, have triggered sharp criticism from Iran and Arab
countries, which accuse Turkey of betraying the interests of
Muslims.
</P>
<P>
The eighth summit of the Organization of Islamic Conference
(OIC) passed a resolution on December 10 in Tehran, capital of
Iran, to indirectly accuse Ankara of establishing close military
relationship with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Israel signed several military and defense accords
in 1996 on training of military staff and cooperation in defense
industry.
</P>
<P>
During the visit here of Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai on December 8-10, The two regional powers agreed in
principle to jointly produce missiles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
