Sunday for a five-years mandate. (Serbia-Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin returned to Kremlin
on Tuesday after recovering from a cold.
</P>
<P>
Ignoring doctors' advice to spend another week at a sanatorium
at Barvikha outside Moscow, Yeltsin insisted on going back to work.
</P>
<P>
"There are none of the traces of the illness left," he said.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to hold a number of working meetings in the
Kremlin before the new year, one of which is a round-table meeting
