Friday. (Russia-Yeltsin-Health)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German real estate tycoon Juergen Schneider was
sentenced by a Frankfurt court to six years and nine months in
prison Tuesday for fraud leading to the biggest real estate
bankruptcy in postwar Germany.
</P>
<P>
The term was exactly one year less than what the prosecution
had demanded last week for Schneider, 63, who was found guilty of
five counts of serious fraud. (Germany-Imprisonment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Maruso Securities Co., a
midsize brokerage house, filed a petition Tuesday with the Tokyo
District Court for permission to start voluntary bankruptcy
proceedings, Kyodo News reported.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo-based brokerage went bankrupt after it failed to
improve its loss-ridden financial situation.
</P>
<P>
Maruso's unconsolidated pretax balance was in the red for the
third consecutive year when it closed its books in March 1997,
with a loss of 1.48 billion yen (about 11 millionU.S. dollars).
(Japan-Securities-Bankruptcy)
</P>
<P>
