HANOI -- A "B52 Blitz Victory Museum" was inaugurated Monday in
Vietnam's capital city of Hanoi, marking the the 25th anniversary
of the "Hanoi--Dien Bien Phu Victory in the Air."
</P>
<P>
The "Dien Bien Phu Victory in the Air" recalled the fight of
the Vietnamese people against the United States in the country.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred fighter-bombers and about 150 B52s operated
daily over North Vietnam between December 18-30,
1972. (Vietnam-Victory-Museum)
</P>
<P>
