<HEADLINE> Ajmal Mian Takes Oath as Pakistan's Chief Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Ajmal Mian took oath Tuesday
as Pakistan's Chief Justice at the Presidential House.
</P>
<P>
Acting President Wasim Sajjad administered the oath of office
in the light of supreme court judgment.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Tuesday, a ten-member bench of the Supreme Court held
in an unanimous decision the appointment of Justice Sajjad Ali
Shah as Chief Justice of Pakistan as invalid.
</P>
<P>
The bench headed by Justice Saiduzzaman Siddiqui in its short
order said that the appointment of Sajjad Ali Shah as the Chief
Justice of the apex court is "invalid, unlawful and
unconstitutional."
</P>
<P>
The bench asked the government to appoint Justice Ajmal Mian as
the Chief Justice.  
</P>
