<HEADLINE> Milutinovic Elected as Serbian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Serbian electoral commission
officially announced the victory of Socialist party candidate
Milan Milutinovic in Serbia's presidential run-off over Vojislav
Seseji.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic, 55, who is Yugoslv foreign minister, was elected
Sunday for a five-year mandate.
</P>
<P>
In the presidential election held on Sunday, more than half of
the registered voters went to the polls, which validated the
election according to the Serbian electoral law.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic pocketed 59.23 percent of the votes, topping his
rival Vojislav Seseji of the Radical Party who won 37.57 percent
of the votes.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic was born on December 19, 1942 in Belgrade and
graduated from the Department of Law in University of Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
He has held various posts in public authorities such as
minister of Science and Education of the Serbian Republic and
director of Serbian National Library.
</P>
<P>
As an intimate friend of President of the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia and his sucessor, Milutinovic's assumption of
presidency will benefit the continuity of the current policies and
the political stability in the republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
