<HEADLINE> Romanian Foreign Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Foreign Minister,
Adrian Severin, resigned Tuesday, but President Emil
Constantinescu has not responded to his resignation.
</P>
<P>
Ion Diaconescu, the head of the ruling National Peasants'
Party, said that the president will accept the resignation.
</P>
<P>
Severin said in September that some heads of the country's
political parties and newspapers are spys of the foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Angered by the allegation, the media and public called for an
immediate explanation.
</P>
<P>
The president ordered an immediate investigation and asked the
concerned department to give the result within two months.
</P>
<P>
He said that if the allegation is not true, Severin has to
resign as the foreign minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
