<HEADLINE> Greek Army Always Ready to Defend Country: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Greek armed forces were always
ready to respond to emergencies, National Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos said today.
</P>
<P>
Tsohatzopoulos made the statement in the northern Greek city of
Thessaloniki when asked by reporters if a serious incident could
happen between Greece and neighboring Turkey next year.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that no one could answer that question with
certainty.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, eight Turkish F-16s and F-4s
warplanes today infringed on the Athens Flight Information Region
near the Aegean islands of Lesvos and Samothrace, but all of them
were intercepted by Greek fighters, Greek Defense Ministry sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Greece and Turkey, rivalries for decades,
have recently deteriorated following the expulsion of diplomats by
the two countries. 
