<HEADLINE> EgyptAir Receives Bomb Warning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- EgyptAir was hoaxed today by a
second bomb warning in less than 10 days, the Middle East News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Thirty minutes after an EgyptAir's flight took off for Japanese
capital Tokyo, Cairo airport was warned by an anonymous call that
a bomb had been planted on the plane.
</P>
<P>
EgyptAir, however, decided not to order back the plane which
was carrying 180 passengers plus a crew of 23.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Egyptian Embassy in Japan was hoaxed by an
anonymous caller that an EgyptAir jet flying from Tokyo to Cairo
had a bomb on board.
</P>
<P>
No bomb was found, but the flight was delayed for four hours.
</P>
<P>
Flights between Tokyo and Cairo have been shelved for some time
due to massive cancellations of trips to Egypt after Islamic
militants killed 58 foreign tourists in Egypt's southern resort
Luxor on November 17. 
</P>
