<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Needs More Psychiatric Professionals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addis Ababa, December 23 (xinhua) -- Of all the medical
fields, psychiatric treatments in Ethiopia remain in negligence
and threatened by lack of professionals, the Ethiopian News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Tiruwork Tafesse, Director of the Amanuel
Hospital Psychiatric Treatments Nursing School, as saying that
the Ethiopian government has recently set up 28 psychiatric
centers nationwide to ward off the health problems of its
population.
</P>
<P>
She, however, disclosed that the country at present has not
had more than nine specialists in the field, which means as many
as 6.2 million Ethiopians have to share one psychiatrist.
</P>
<P>
Tafesse called for efforts to expand psychiatric profession in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
There are over 6,000 mental patients in Ethiopia who should be
treated as inpatients, according to the report. 
