<HEADLINE> Traffic Death Toll Hits 468 in December in S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents have
claimed 468 lives in South Africa since December 1, mainly due to
speeding, South African traffic authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure is 41 more than the death toll announced by the
National Traffic Information Center Monday.
</P>
<P>
As Christmas is drawing near, traffic on South African roads
are expected to increase three-fold from Wednesday, the day
before Christmas, South African Press Association quoted the road
safety "Arrive Alive" campaign as saying.
</P>
<P>
Gauteng Province, where Pretoria and business capital
Johannesburg are located, registered the most fatalities of 87.
It is followed by Eastern Cape, with 81, and Kwazulu-Natal, with
72, the campaign said.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 people died in road accidents in the Christmas
season last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
