<HEADLINE> 2.532 Bln Dlr UN Budget for 1998-99 Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly of
the United Nations has approved an appropriation of some 2.532
billion U.S. dollars for the 1998-1999 budget, which incorporates
elements of the secretary-general's reform proposals.
</P>
<P>
A release from the spokesman's office today also said that this
reflected a reduction of some 61.2 million dollars from the
revised appropriations of about 2.603 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
In adopting the resolution late Monday night, the General
Assembly stressed that the reform proposals would be implemented
with full respect for relevant mandates of the assembly.
</P>
<P>
The assembly also decided to, among other measures, to increase
the total in the development account to about 13 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
