<HEADLINE> American Charged With Spying to Leave Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- American citizen Richard
Bliss, who was arrested and charged with espionage in Russia, will
be allowed to leave under an agreement with the Russian security
service, the U.S. State Department said today.
</P>
<P>
"We understand that Mr. Bliss may depart Rostov-on-Don, Russia,
today on a Qualcomm chartered aircraft for the United States," a
spokesman for the State Department said.
</P>
<P>
