<HEADLINE> Jordan Calls on Israel to Implement Peace Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Jordan today called on Israel to
implement the peace agreements it signed with its Arab neighbors
to revive the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Israel should step up its efforts to carry out the peace
accords to advance its talks with the Palestinians, Jordan's Prime
Minister Abdul Salam Majali said during a meeting with Yossi
Beilin, Israeli Knesset (parliament) member of the Labor Party.
</P>
<P>
Beilin, a former Labor government minister, arrived here today
for a short visit.
</P>
<P>
Intensive efforts are needed to break the current deadlock in
the peace process and push it forward, Majali said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that the negotiations between Israel
and Syria and Lebanon can restart.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian-Israeli peace talks were suspended last year after a
series of suicide bombings in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Majali also stressed the importance of economic cooperation
between Jordan, the Palestinians and Israel in achieving peace.
</P>
<P>
Beilin agreed to it, saying that the best solution to the
current crisis is to strengthen economic cooperation among the
three sides.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Israeli Prime Minister Benyamin Netanyahu's recent
claim that the West Bank is part of Israel, Beilin said that
Israel should not draw a map for the future of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
It is unwise for Israel to do so without the participation of
the Palestinians. Instead, they should work together on this
issue, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
