<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Offers List of Jordanian Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has officially offered
Jordan a list of Jordanian prisoners in Iraq's jails on the
kingdom's request, confirming that all the 66 jailbirds got fair
trial and were being treated well.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi Embassy in Jordan sent the list to the Jordanian
Foreign Ministry Monday after the Jordanian government
officially asked Iraq to provide the information about all the
Jordanians jailed in Iraqi prisons, embassy officials told
Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
The list also contained the names of Jordanian prisoners who
were set free during the last two years on Iraqi President
Saddam Hussein's order.
</P>
<P>
The number of Jordanian prisoners in Iraqi jails are
officially estimated at over 100 but unofficially at over 600.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has just officially declared to suspend the death
sentence on a Jordanian prisoner in an effort to defuse the
tension caused by its execution of five Jordanians this month.
</P>
<P>
The suspension of death sentence came amid reports that
Jordan and Iraq will strengthen their economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Iraq executed four Jordanian prisoners on charge of smuggling
car spare parts on December 8, then planned to free 140 Jordanian
prisoners, but executed another Jordanian on charge of murder on
December 10.
</P>
<P>
Jordan expelled seven Iraqi diplomats in retaliation of the
executions and expressed perplexity with Iraq's contradictory
actions.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Iraq used to be firm allies before and during the
Gulf War in 1991. But after that, the bilateral ties suffered a
setback as Jordan was eager to distance itself away from Iraq to
end international alienation.
</P>
<P>
However, the ties has been picking up in recent years as
Iraq begins to provide the kingdom with more and more oil
at discount prices and keeps increasing the volume of imports
from Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Iraq provided Jordan with oil worth 625 million U.S. dollars
this year, a 7 percent increase over the previous year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
