<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-23 20:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Underlines Importance of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami today underlined the importance of environment protection
in the country, saying that environment does not contradict
development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of Iran's Supreme Council of
Environmental Affairs, Khatami said that Iran is rapidly moving
through development phase, but it needs to see the issue of
environment does not stand in the way of progress.
</P>
<P>
He said that a well-balanced environmental design should be
defined in relation to the patterns of the country's development,
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president stressed that it was necessary to
include the issue of environment in the educational programs as
well. He proposed to create departments of environment at the
ministries of oil, industries and the Organization of Planning and
Budget.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by Vice President in Environmental
Affairs and head of the Organization of Environmental Protection
Masoumeh Ebtekar, and ministers of housing, agriculture, health,
education, construction and jihad as well as some other top
officials.
</P>
<P>
So far the main environmental challenges for the Iranian
government are the issues of pollution in the Persian Gulf,
the Caspian Sea, and air pollution in some big cities such
as Tehran and Tabriz. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
