<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 260 More Mosques Under Egyptian Government's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Ministry of Waqfs
(religious endowments) today decided to place 260 more mosques
under its supervision.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Waqfs Mahmoud Hamdi Zaqzouq told the press that the
decision is part of the continuous drive to isolate religious
extremists.
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 2,219 mosques are under the supervision of
the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Zaqzouq disclosed that Egypt has planned to bring all the
mosques under the supervision of the Ministry of Waqfs by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that there are about 30,000 mosques in
Egypt. But unofficial figures put the number at about 50,000.
</P>
<P>
Under a law designed to protect religious services from the
unqualified, imams are required to apply for a license from the
government before they can deliver sermons in mosques since
December last year.
</P>
<P>
There are about 52.2 million Muslims in Egypt, accounting for
87 percent of the population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
