<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Urges Full Clearance of Wage Arrears </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
instructed on Wednesday that the federal and regional authorities
must fully clear wage arrears by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said, at a meeting with First Vice Prime Minister Boris
Nemtsov, that the promise made by him and the government to pay
all wage arrears to Russian workers before the beginning of 1998
must be kept and no further delay will be allowed.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov was quoted by the Itar-Tass news agency as saying that
as far as the federal government is concerned, it has fulfilled
its obligation by transferring 11.3 trillion rubles to the local
authorities on December 23 and the task now rests primarily with
them.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov is optimistic that wage arrears will be fully cleared
in most regions. But in some regions such as Primorye,
Krasnoyardk, Chita and Khakas, the task will be difficult.
</P>
<P>
President Yeltsin told Nemtsov that neither the federal nor the
regional authorities should break the promise.
</P>
<P>
"This is one state and the wage arrears must be fully paid off
in the public sector by January 1. The word must be kept."
emphasized Yeltsin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
