<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Zhu Rongji on China's Economic Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Zhu
Rongji today fully affirmed the new achievements China has made
this year in its reform, opening-up and the socialist
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
While analyzing the country's current economic situation, the
vice-premier, who is also a member of the Standing Committee of
the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee, pointed out the contradictions and problems now
existing in China's national economy, and made explicit
requirements on how to solve them.
</P>
<P>
Zhu was speaking about China's economic situation to 3,200
senior Chinese officials, including newly elected members and
alternate members of the Central Committee of the Chinese
Communist Party, executives of key state businesses and senior
army officers.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice premier also briefed the officials on the
guidelines of the recent Central Economic Work Conference.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed the belief that under the leadership of the Party
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and with the joint
efforts of the people, more successes will be accomplished next
year in every field of work.
</P>
<P>
The lecture was jointly sponsored by the Publicity Department
of the Communist Party of China Central Committee, the General
Political Department of the People's Liberation Army, the Beijing
Municipal Party Committee and several other departments.
</P>
<P>
The lecture was presided over by Ding Guangen, member of the
Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat, of the CPC Central
Committee, and head of the Publicity Department of the CPC Central
Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
