<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dragons Outpoint Squirrels in Chinese Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Despite its home advantage,
Zhejiang Squirrels suffered their miserable defeat against Jiangsu
Dragons 64-85 in the 10th round of the Chinese Basketball League
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The home squad made the fans aghast as many a cagers committed
unforced errors time and again while the visiting side displayed
their upperhands from the very beginning.
</P>
<P>
The Dragons established a 52-28 lead at half break and even
scored the highest margin of 27 points before they eventually
rounded up the victory.
</P>
<P>
The home fans even booed the local cagers as they were caught
in an inconvertible dilemma and thunders of applauses awarded to
ace player Hu Weidong whenever he scored the basket for the
visiting squad.
</P>
<P>
Hu Weidong, ace player in the national team, scored the
game-high 26 points for the Dragons while the Squirrels cried for
their superstar of any significance.
</P>
<P>
In Jinan of Shandong province, local Flaming Bulls defeated
Liaoning Hunters 77-68 from a 37-35 half advantage.
</P>
<P>
The game witnessed the neck-to-neck clashes as both sides
resorted to double-midfielders tactics with swift attacks and
quick defense to see the scoredboard tied from 18-all, 20-all and
35-all.
</P>
<P>
After the break, the Bulls once surged ahead with big margins
but committed seven fouls in five minutes to enable their
opponents to claw back for a 53-all deadlock.
</P>
<P>
In the last three minutes, Gong Xiaobin scored seven points to
pace the home squad to savor the hard victory.
</P>
<P>
In Chendu, Sichuan Pandas rallied back to outwit Lianhang
Eagles 82-73 from a 31-39 half deficit while Jinan Army lost its
home game to Shanghai Sharks 76-81.
</P>
<P>
In other two games, Guangdong Tigers suffered their home defeat
against Bayi Rockets 79-88 as they lagged behind 31-47 in the
first half, while Beijing Ducks whitewashed Shenyang Lions 88-58
as the Ducks established a comfortable half advantage of 40-22.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
