<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Compete in Wrestling Internationals in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Southern Oregon University
free-style wrestling team has announced its readiness to compete
in the 16th Fajr international wrestling competitions to be held
here next month.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA said that the U.S. university
squad has confirmed its participation in a letter to the Iranian
Wrestling Federation. However, IRNA did not mention when and how
the letter was received.
</P>
<P>
In the letter, the American squad asked for information about
the number of athletes allowed to participate in the tournament
and other matters concerned.
</P>
<P>
In a competition in Russia earlier this year, the American
wrestling officials, including the head of the U.S. free-style
wrestling team, expressed readiness to sent a team to Tehran, the
report added.
</P>
<P>
It would be the first U.S. sports team to take part in Iran's
annual sports meets to celebrate the anniversary of the Islamic
Revolution in 1979, after which Washington and Iran severed their
diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Both Iran and the Unitd States took some small and cautious
steps to low down their hostile tones this year, particularly
after the presidential elections in May when the moderate
intellectual Mohammad Khatami was elected Iranian president.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
