<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chernobyl Reconstruction to be Put in Tenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) will soon hold tenders for
reconstructing the crumbling shelter encasing Chernobyl's fourth
reactor, the Ukrainian News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
But actual repairs will likely come next century as much of the
preliminary research for the project has yet to be done, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Seventeen countries have pledged or already paid out a total of
165 million U.S. dollars to finance repairs to the reactor's
11-year-old sarcophagus. EBRD, which administers the Chernobyl
Shelter Fund, has agreed to provide a total of 387.5 million
dollars to the project by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
"This is more than enough to start work on the project," said
Vince Novak, project manager for the EBRD Chernobyl Shelter Fund.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine will contribute 50 million dollars in labor and
construction materials towards the project. The leading Western
industrialized nations will ultimately offer 300 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
It will take almost a decade to repair the protective
sarcophagus hurriedly erected in 1987 to seal the radioactive
core of the No. 4 reactor, which was the source of the world's
worst civil nuclear accident in April 1986 . 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
