<HEADLINE> CPPCC National Committee Chairman's Meeting Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The 50th Chairman's meeting of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) was held in the Chinese capital of
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, presided over by CPPCC National Committee Chairman
Li Ruihuan and attended by nine vice-chairmen, decided that the
23rd meeting of the Standing Committee of the Eighth CPPCC
National Committee will be convened on January 19, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The chairman's meeting proposed that the first session of the
Ninth CPPCC National Committee be convened in early March 1998,
with the specific date to be decided by the 23rd meeting of the
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting also examined and approved in principle the work
report of the Standing Committee of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee, which will be submit to its 23rd meeting for
examination. 
