<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao's Exports to Canada Up 28.6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Macao's exports to Canada in the
first eight months of this year reached 36.83 million Canadian
dollars (25.68 million U.S. dollars), up 28.6 percent over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Canadian exports to Macao in the January-August period hit 2.61
million Canadian dollars (about 1.82 million dollars), up 159.9
percent over the same period of last year, Wednesday's Macao Daily
News reported, quoting Canadian statistics.
</P>
<P>
The figures meant a trade deficit of 34.22 million Canadian
dollars (23.86 million dollars) for Canada, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It added that Canada's imports from Macao only accounted for a
tiny 0.02 percent of all its imports. Most of the imports from
Macao were garments, batteries, fishing articles, toys, electronic
parts, canned food, plastic products and gloves.
</P>
<P>
Canada's exports to Macao included telecommunications
equipment, yarns, newsprint, farm produce, construction equipment
and aircraft parts. The exports to Macao accounted for only 0.01
percent of all Canada's exports.
</P>
<P>
Canada has seen a trade deficit with Macao for five years since
1992, the report said, adding that Macao-produced garments have
been extremely welcomed in Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
