<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao, Beijing Launch Joint Study of Macao Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Experts in Macao and Beijing
have launched a joint study of the economic growth of Macao, and a
comprehensive report will be submitted in a year.
</P>
<P>
Wong Ho Keong, deputy director of the Macao Research Center of
the University of Macao, told the Macao Daily News Tuesday that
his center is co-conducting the probe into Macao's economic growth
with the Hong Kong and Macao Research Center of Beijing
University.
</P>
<P>
The study, "The strategic choice for the sustainable economic
and social development of Macao," will last one whole year.
</P>
<P>
Wong said that the joint study will incorporate opinions of
different sides, making it more reliable and balanced.
</P>
<P>
The key of study will be the readjustment of Macao's economic
role, the expansion of Macao's growth potential and the way to
enhance Macao's competitiveness, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
Following the study and analysis, a comprehensive report,
together with proposals, will be submitted for reference to
related departments in China's inland and the Macao Government.
</P>
<P>
How to help Macao step out of its current economic doldrums has
been a hot topic of study over the past few years. Similar studies
were undertaken by research bodies in Macao and China's inland.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
