<HEADLINE> S. Africa Okeys UN Sea Law Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has
ratified the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea,
three years after the treaty went into force.
</P>
<P>
Documents confirming South Africa's ratification were
deposited at the U.N. Tuesday, making South Africa the 123rd
member of the convention, the Department of Foreign Affairs
announced today.
</P>
<P>
"South Africa, in ratifying the convention, demonstrated to
the international community that it is a responsible role-player
in marine and maritime affairs, and that it is committed to the
proper management of human activities pertaining to the oceans,"
the department said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The convention will come into force for South Africa on
January 22.
</P>
<P>
The convention, which regulates human activities regarding the
use of the oceans and their resources, took effect on November
16, 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
