<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan to Expand Grain Export to Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan will expand grain
export to Asian countries while maintaining its market share in
the traditional destinations, said Kazakh President Nazarbayev in
Akmola on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan's traditional grain markets have been the members of
the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), said Nazarbayev at a
national agricultural meeting, but it will now try to explore
grain market in Turkey, Pakistan and China.
</P>
<P>
The country's domestic grain market has been sluggish and grain
prices are often lower than production costs due to the gross
inefficiency of the agro-industrial complexes.
</P>
<P>
This situation will adversely affect the country's grain
production and the overall agricultural development in the future.
</P>
<P>
To solve the problems, the Kazakh government has decided to
strengthen the management of agricultural credit, break the
monopoly on grain storage and transport, create a national grain
union to protect the interests of grain producers, improve the
supply system to enable farmers a direct access to farming
supplies, and attract foreign investment and technologies.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan produced 13 million tons of grain this year, which
can not only meet the domestic demand but also have a considerable
surplus for export. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
