<HEADLINE> Netanyahu Hiding Info From Ministers: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu is keeping his cabinet members in the dark
while creating false impressions about the negotiating process
with the Palestinians, a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post quoted a senior Israeli government source as
saying that Netanyahu is concealing "the picture being drawn for
him" by the Americans from his ministers.
</P>
<P>
In other words, the source said, Netanyahu allegedly knows
exactly which and how much territories the United States wants
Israel to hand over to the Palestinians in the second phase of
Israeli troops redeployment, but is withholding this information.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the source made the remarks just after
Netanyahu and most of his cabinet ministers Tuesday completed a
helicopter tour of the West Bank areas that may be included in the
next pullback.
</P>
<P>
The source also assailed Netanyahu for hiding the fact that
pressure is being brought by the U.S. simply because he does not
want his ministers to break ranks before the national budget of
1998 is put to a vote in the Knesset (parliament) at the end of
this month.
</P>
<P>
"But he is wrong about that," the source went on, adding
"because after the budget is approved everything will blow up."
</P>
<P>
He noted that because of the concealment of the truth, some
hard-liners in the cabinet still delude themselves to believe that
a withdrawal from only 6 percent of the West Bank will suffice.
</P>
<P>
The source stressed that Netanyahu's handling of the second
phase troops pullback in the West Bank is causing profound
dissension in the highest levels of his cabinet, while at the same
time creating a potentially irreparable rift between him and his
closest political allies.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister David Levy, one of the cabinet's most
outspoken moderates, did not join the West Bank trip. Levy accused
his cabinet colleagues of thinking that they can procrastinate
endlessly handing over territories to the Palestinians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
