<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Home-Made Car Exported to US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China exported its first car
to the United States today. The buyer is General Motors Corp.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that a Chinese-built car has been exported
to a developed country since the founding of New China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The car, called Zhonghua, was designed and built by the
Beijing Zhonghua Automobile Corp., Ltd. Its body, made from new
materials used in the aviation industry, has a strong resistance
to shock and erosion.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,800 Zhonghua cars have been sold domestically and
many manufacturers from the U.S., Japan, Germany, Sweden and
Canada have expressed their interest in buying the car.
</P>
<P>
The Zhonghua Automobile Corp., Ltd. was established in 1995.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
