<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Art Activities to Celebrate New Year, Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 art performances
will be staged in Beijing as a New Year's gift to local residents,
a spokeswoman for the Ministry of Culture said today.
</P>
<P>
A dozen famous symphony orchestras and art troupes will hold a
variety of New Year's concerts for 50 nights during the coming New
Year and Spring Festival, the Chinese lunar New Year which falls
on Jan. 28, 1998, she said.
</P>
<P>
The concerts will include not only traditional western concerts
of choral, symphonic and chamber music for Christmas and New Year,
but also concerts featuring Chinese film and folk songs, she said.
</P>
<P>
For 21 nights the National Ballet Troupe of China will perform
"Don Quixote," "Sleeping Beauty," "Giselle" and "Swan Lake", as
well as the modern Chinese ballet "The Red Detachment of Women."
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Culture, China Central Television Station and
many state art troupes will also present 20 holiday celebrations
of songs, dances and acrobatic programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
