<HEADLINE> China to Mark 90th Anniversary of Chinese Modern Drama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China will host a series of
activities from December 25 to January 11, 1998, to mark
the 90th anniversary of the birth of modern drama in China.
</P>
<P>
"More than 2,000 experts and drama performers nationwide will
attend a variety of performance and celebration activities," a
spokesman for the Ministry of Culture said at a press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they will hold discussions on the history,
development, and future of Chinese drama, he said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 18 dramas will be staged during the two-week event,
including "Thunderstorm", "Running River", "Veteran", and "Old Man
and His Crickets".
</P>
<P>
The sponsors of the celebration activities are
the Ministry of Culture and the China Federation of Literary and
Art Circles .
</P>
<P>
Chinese modern drama started with Wang Zhongsheng in 1907 when
his drama troupe Chun Yang (Spring Sun) put on stage "Uncle Tom's
Cabin" in shanghai as the first Chinese drama. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
