<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Make New Breakthroughs in Enterprise Reform (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- In the coming three years,
China will speed up the reform of state enterprises, so as to help
most large and medium-sized state firms get rid of the current
difficult situation, while the reform of small state companies
will be completed within two years.
</P>
<P>
Lu Yonghua, Director of the Research Office of the State
Commission for Economic Restructuring, made the remarks during an
interview with Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
These goals set by the government show that the time has been
ripe for making key breakthroughs in the restructuring of state
enterprises and that the reform has entered into an overall and
crucial stage.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the new round of enterprise reform
will be focused on adoption of the modern enterprise system
through clarifying property rights and responsibilities,
separating government and enterprise functions, and adopting
scientific managerial methods.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be made to reinvigorate large and medium-sized
state companies, especially 1,000 firms in important industries,
while the government will give up its direct control over small
enterprises through various means including merger, bankruptcy,
contracting, leasing and joint stock.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
