<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Use of Foreign Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today
spoke highly of China's efforts in using foreign capital over the
past two decades and urged the relevant departments to do a good
job related to the introduction of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with participants at the National Conference on
Introduction of Foreign Investment in the Great Hall of the
People, Jiang said the use of foreign capital constitutes a major
component of China's opening-up, which is an important part of
Deng Xiaoping Theory and an inevitable road to follow to realize
modernizations and to bring about national revitalization.
</P>
<P>
The use of foreign capital while learning the advanced
technology and management experience has in one way helped to
promote the sustained growth of the national economy and enhanced
the comprehensive national strength and the ability to compete in
the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called for absorbing foreign investment in a diversified
way and, in the process, he noted, it it essential to integrate
the use of foreign investment with the country's domestic economic
growth strategy.
</P>
<P>
Confronted with the growing competitions between the nations in
fields of economy, science and technology and comprehensive
national strength, China is now meeting with both new
opportunities and new challenges, Jiang said. The country should
strive to update its opening to a still more multi-faceted,
diversified and wider setup, so as to advance its use of overseas
investment to a new, higher level.
</P>
<P>
In an endeavor to utilize foreign capital well, emphasis should
be placed on raising quality and performance of the national
economy and enhancing the comprehensive national strength and
capability for international competitions by adhering to the
policy of using foreign capital in a still more active, rational
and effective way, he said. Moreover, he added, active efforts
should be made to guide foreign investment into agriculture,
high-tech and infrastructure sectors, as well as to
export-oriented production projects.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of ranking officials and representatives working in
foreign trade and economic sectors from across China attended the
three-day conference, whose main theme is to map out a blueprint
for the country's use of foreign capital in the 21st century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
