<HEADLINE> China to Improve Basic Social Security System in Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Introducing and improving the
basic social security system in urban area will be the most
important task for civil affairs work in 1998, a senior official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Introducing the system for urban residents is vital to
reforming the traditional social relief system and perfecting the
social security system, State Councillor Li Guixiang told a
national conference on civil affairs which closed here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that the system can help maintain social stability
and advance economic reforms, while giving a full play to the
superiority of the socialist system.
</P>
<P>
"The sooner it is instituted throughout the country, the
greater benefits it will bring to economic and social
development," Li noted.
</P>
<P>
More than 270 cities, or over 40 percent of the country's
total, have introduced the system. Some 70 cities have instituted
the system over the past three months.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Civil Affairs has already required all cities
above the prefecture level, two-thirds of the cities at the county
level and one-third of the county seats to introduce the basic social
security system in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
