<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Session Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The 29th session of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC)
opened here today. Three new laws on such issues as blood
donations, prices, earthquake prevention and disaster relief are
expected to be passed.
</P>
<P>
NPC Standing Committee chairman Qiao Shi presided over the
plenary meeting this morning.
</P>
<P>
The drafts of the new laws were discussed at previous NPC
Standing Committee sessions.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the session will deliberate proposed drafts on
higher education as well as a national new on high-tech industrial
development zones.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the session will examine the draft of a decision
on convening the First Session of the Ninth National People's
Congress, which will be held early next year.
</P>
<P>
The participants will also listen to reports submitted by the
State Council and NPC Standing Committee examination groups on the
country's financial situation and on the implementation of laws
concerning agriculture and water resources based on inspections.
</P>
</TEXT>
