<HEADLINE> Bombay Stock Index Loses 33.42 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 24 (Xinhua)-- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday lost 33.42 points to
3607.69 as against Tuesday's close of 3641.11.
</P>
<P>
The national index dropped 13.45 points to 1563.77 from
previous close of 1577.22.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and us dollar index were quoted down at 349.13 and
148.62 points compared with Tuesday's close of 350.97 and 149.18
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Reflecting early selling pressure triggered by reports of South
Korean stocks crash with its currency touching a new record low
against the U.S. dollar, the BSE sensitive index Wednesday fell
back sharply to the day's low of 3549.50 during the first half.
</P>
<P>
However, it was up after mid-session to close at 3607.69.
</P>
<P>
The BSE market is likely to move in a narrow range now onwards
till the year-end in the absence of foreign funds, brokers said.
</P>
</TEXT>
