<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian Striker Joins English Club </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Romanian striker Viorel
Moldovan joined England Premier League team Coventry in a club
record 3.25 million pound (about 5.2 million U.S. dollars)
transfer from Swiss club Grasshoppers.
</P>
<P>
Moldovan, 25, scored nine goals in World Cup qualifying games
to lift Romania advance to the 1998 France World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Moldovan scored 77 goals in 103 games for Neuchatel Xamax and
Grasshoppers in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Moldovan signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with the Sky
Blues worth around 2 million pounds (about 3.2 million
U.S. dollars). He becomes the second Romanian playing in the
Premier League, joining Chelsea's Dan Petrescu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
