<HEADLINE> Scientists, Technicians Urged to Boost Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists and
technicians should make greater contributions to the country's
economic development, said Wen Jiabao, a member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting of China Association for Science and
Technology (CAST), Wen said that the nearly 20 million Chinese
scientists and technicians should further intergrate science and
technology with economic development, expand academic exchanges,
and strengthen the work of popularizing science and technology
with the public.
</P>
<P>
He added that China should strengthen its research in basic
sciences, and at the same time develop high-technologies and turn
advanced technology into a productive force.
</P>
<P>
He said that China should improve its environment of
international technological exchanges to narrow the gap with
developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao, president of CAST, said that next year -- the
20th anniversary of Deng Xiaoping's statement that "Science and
Technology is the No.1 productive force" and the 40th anniversary
of the founding of CAST -- the association will expand
international academic exchanges and train more high-quality
scientists and technicians.  
</P>
</TEXT>
