<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Ten International News Events of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are top ten
world news events in 1997 selected by the Xinhua News Agency:
</P>
<P>
1. British Scientists Successfully Clone Sheep Using Cell of
</P>
<P>
Adult Sheep, Making Breakthrough in Bio-Engineering
</P>
<P>
British scientists at Edinburgh's Roslin Institute announced on
February 23 that they had created a lamb, named "Dolly," from a
single cell taken from the udder of an adult sheep, the world's
first clone of an adult animal.
</P>
<P>
The success is a breakthrough in bio-engineering, but it soon
aroused concerns over its possible negative effects on ecological
environment and ethical guidelines if the cloning technology is
applied in duplicating human beings.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Educational Scientific and Cultural
Organization (UNESCO) adopted a document against human cloning, in
Paris on November 11.
</P>
<P>
2. Five Nations Strike Accord on Border Arms Reduction,
</P>
<P>
Creating New Model of Safeguarding Regional Security
</P>
<P>
Presidents of China, Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and
Tajikistan signed an agreement in Moscow on April 24 on reduction
of armed forces in their border areas.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, the first of its kind in the Asia Pacific region
and also a result of over seven years of negotiations, manifested
a new model for safeguarding regional security which is different
from the cold-war mentality.
</P>
<P>
It represents a fresh move in handling inter-state relations
and regional security issues and will exert a positive impact on
world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
3. Thick Smog Produced by Big Forest Fires in Indonesia Affect
</P>
<P>
Many countries
</P>
<P>
Indonesia suffered from big forest fires that started in
Sumatra and Kalimantan in April and raged over five months.
</P>
<P>
The fires caused a direct economic loss of more than 3 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The thick smog spread in all directions and affected the health
of many people in Indonesia and several other surrounding
South-East Asian countries and Australia.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the haze was blamed for the cancellation of many
flights and collision of boats and vehicles in Indonesia as well
as the crash of a Garuda Airbus, in which all 234 on board were
killed.
</P>
<P>
4. Central Africa Sees Consecutive Shift of Power
</P>
<P>
Lauren Kabila declared himself head of state of Zaire and
changed the name of the country to the Democratic Republic of
Congo on May 17, putting an end to the 32-year rule of Mobutu Sese
Seko in the country.
</P>
<P>
Later in the neighboring Republic of Congo there occurred a
political turmoil in which former President Denis Sassou Nguesso
overthrew President Pascal Lissouba. Sassou was inaugurated as
President on October 25.
</P>
<P>
5. Hong Kong Returns to China and "One Country, Two Systems"
</P>
<P>
Policy Acclaimed Worldwide
</P>
<P>
On July 1 at a Hong Kong handover ceremony, Chinese President
Jiang Zemin solemnly proclaimed to the world China's resumption of
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong. He also announced the
establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) of the People's Republic of China at another ceremony for
the inauguration of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong marks an end to the 100-year national
humiliation of the Chinese people. It also symbolizes an important
step in the great cause of achieving national reunification.
China's policy of "one country, two systems" has received
worldwide praise.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index on Wednesday rose 0.78 points to close at 709.07.
</P>
<P>
The Index, introduced in August 1995, tracks the overall
performance of China's 32 state enterprises listed on the Hong
Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index fell 4.27 points from the
 previous session to close at 1,231.13.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index comprises 50 most actively-traded
stocks of middle capitalization companies on the local bourse to
help investors and fund managers diversify their portfolios.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index lost
10.33 points to close at 1,686.38.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index tracks the
performance of 32 locally-listed companies with a significant
equity interest held by entities in China.
</P>
<P>
The three segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng
Index (HSI) Services Limited, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang
Seng Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Ten World News Events of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A financial storm touched off by the devaluation of the
Thailand currency Baht swept Southeast Asia in July and then
spread to Northeast Asia and other parts of the world, resulting
in drastic turmoil in the monetary and stock markets of many
countries and upsetting their economy to various degrees.
</P>
<P>
7. First Successful Exploration on Mars Marks Another Step
</P>
<P>
Taken by Mankind in Conquering Universe
</P>
<P>
On July 4, Pathfinder, an American spacecraft, landed on the
Mars. The little mobile rover, Sojourner, released by the
spacecraft, sent back clear images of the Martian landscape,
sunrises and frozen ice clouds, which enables mankind to have a
better understanding of the planet for the first time.
</P>
<P>
8. NATO Invites Three East European Nations to Join Bloc,
</P>
<P>
Resulting in Change in European Security Pattern
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization decided at a summit held
in Madrid in July to first invite Poland, Hungary and the Czech
Republic to join the bloc. The move brought about a significant
change in the post-war geopolitical situation and security pattern
in Europe. NATO has planned to further its expansion toward central
and eastern Europe despite Russia's strong opposition.
</P>
<P>
9. China, U.S. Agree to Build Constructive Strategic
</P>
<P>
Partnership During President Jiang Zemin's Visit to U.S.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin paid a state visit to the United
States from October 26 to November 2, the first by a Chinese head
of state to the U.S. in 12 years. A joint statement was issued
which pledges to build a constructive strategic partnership
between the two countries and decides on making exchanges of visit
by the presidents of the two countries. This historic visit shows
that China-U.S. relations have entered a new period of
development.
</P>
<P>
10. Leaders of East Asian Nations Gather for the First Time,
</P>
<P>
Consulting on Building 21st century-oriented Partnership
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN-China-Japan-South Korea and China-ASEAN informal
leaders' meetings were held on December 15 and 16 respectively,
the first such meetings involving these countries. China and ASEAN
issued a joint statement which agrees to establish a partnership
of good-neighborliness and mutual trust oriented to the 21st
century. The signing of the statement shows that the China-ASEAN
relationship has opened a new chapter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
