<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Arrives in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen arrived here today for a three-day
official visit to Egypt at the invitation of his Egyptian
counterpart Amr Moussa.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued at the airport, Qian spoke highly
of the time-honored friendship between Egypt and China.
</P>
<P>
"Despite drastic changes in international and regional
situations, the sincere and strong friendship between the Chinese
and Egyptian peoples based on mutual respect and understanding has
constantly been deepened, and cooperation scope has been expanded
day by day," he said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have always supported, and cooperated with,
each other in international affairs, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe, in the current new world situation, more exchange
of visits by leaders of the two countries are conducive to
deepening mutual understanding, expanding consensus, promoting
friendship and cooperation," Qian said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister also highlighted the significant
role of Egypt in the Middle East, Africa and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Qian said he expected to exchange ideas with Moussa and other
Egyptian leaders on "boosting Sino-Egyptian ties, the Mideast
peace process and other global and regional issues of common
concern."
</P>
<P>
Qian and Moussa are expected to hold talks in the Egyptian
Foreign Ministry at noon. Qian also will meet with President Hosni
Mubarak, Prime Minister Kamal El-Ganzouri as well as Secretary
General of the Arab League Abdul Esmat-Meguid on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"I believe my visit (to Cairo) will be conducive to the
enhancement of existing Sino-Egyptian friendly and cooperative
relations and to the promotion of the cause of peace in the Middle
East," he added.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is the last leg of Qian's current Middle East tour which
has already taken him to Lebanon, Syria, Israel and the
Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
Qian has visited Egypt several times before and he last came
here with Chinese President Jiang Zemin in May 1996. 
</P>
