<HEADLINE> Pirated Video Compact Discs Seized by HK Customs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong customs officers
confiscated more than 130,000 copies of pirated video compact
discs worth about 4 million HK dollars (504,000 U.S. dollars) last
Sunday, local Customs and Excise Department announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers of Sha Tau Kok Control Point, between Hong
Kong and the Chinese mainland, intercepted a lorry departing for
Shenzhen, Hong Kong's next-door neighbor on the mainland, for
search and found the seizure inside the cargo compartment.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old driver was arrested and later released on bail,
pending further investigation. The lorry was impounded, pending
forfeiture.
</P>
<P>
"Customs officers from the Intellectual Property Investigation
Bureau will continue to trace the mastermind of the case in order
to display their determination to eradicate piracy activities in
Hong Kong," said a spokesman for the Customs and Excise
Department.  
</P>
