<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wu Yi on China's Introduction of Foreign Investment (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China's successful absorption
of foreign investment during the past two decades has played a key
role in promoting sustained economic growth and the overall reform
and opening-up in the country, said Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Wu Yi here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu delivered a report at a national conference on foreign
investment which closed today, elaborating on China's achievements
in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
From 1979 to November 1997, she said, China approved more than
302,400 foreign-funded enterprises involving contracted investment
of 513.42 billion U.S. dollars. Of that committed investment, 216.6
billion U.S. dollars has actually been put to use.
</P>
<P>
The most rapid increase in foreign investment has occurred
in the five years following 1992, however, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Since then China has approved 241,317 foreign-funded projects
involving 417.698 billion U.S. dollars of contracted investment, of
which 151.537 billion U.S. dollars have been used. The foreign
funding already spent accounted for 13.94 percent of the the
country's total investment in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
Wu said foreign investment has fueled the sustained, rapid and
sound development of the nation's economy and improved social
stability.
</P>
<P>
By introducing foreign funding China has increased its
financial income, created job opportunities and upgraded the
people's living standard.
</P>
<P>
At present, more than 17.5 million people are working for the
145,000 foreign-financed enterprises, accounting for 10 percent of
the country's non-rural labor force.
</P>
<P>
During the 1992-1996 period taxation on foreign companies,
mainly from foreign-funded enterprises, reached 211.998 billion
yuan, with an annual increase rate of 58.11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The taxation on foreign companies in 1996 accounted for 11.88
percent of the year's total taxes on industrial and commercial
companies, compared to 4.25 percent in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The absorption of foreign funding has also emancipated ideas,
pushed economic restructuring and stimulated the formation of a
market economy, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
During the last two decades or so, the establishment of joint
ventures and cooperative enterprises have spurred on technical
innovation at more than 120,000 state-owned or collectively-owned
enterprises, and a large number of technical and management
professionals have emerged.
</P>
<P>
The state or collectively-owned economic elements within mixed
ownerships has increased these enterprises' value along with the
rapid growth of the mixed economy.
</P>
<P>
This has effectively promoted the transfer of the traditional
ownership structure, and has an important impact on the formation
of a development mode which keeps the public-owned economy in a
dominant place and allows economically diverse forms to develop
side-by-side.
</P>
<P>
This has also played an active role on the formulation of
China's basic economic system at this primary stage of socialism.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
