<HEADLINE> China's Top Diver Dropped from World Championship Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese top women diver Wang
Rui was dropped from the Chinese team for January's World Swimming
Championships in Perth, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who won four titles in international meets this year,
has withdrawn from the 11-day championships because of nagging
neck and back injuries, Shi Tianshu, director of the China
Swimming Administrative Center, confirmed here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The diver from Beijing is hailed as heir apparent to China's
three-time Olympic champion Fu Mingxia, who retired after winning
two gold medals in the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Wang started the year of 1997 with a platform title at the
Beijing international diving meet in January. She then triumphed
in New Zealand, Australia and the United States and ended the year
with a gold medal from the Eighth National Games in October.
</P>
<P>
Wang jumped out of oblivion as she upset Fu Mingxia in the
Seventh Chinese National Games four years ago. 
</P>
