<HEADLINE> International Terrorist Condemned to Life Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Ilich Ramirez Sanchez, also
known as Carlos, was condemned early Wednesday to life
imprisonment by the Assize Court of Paris for the murder of three
people in June 1975.
</P>
<P>
The life imprisonment was recommended by Attorney General Gino
Necchi Monday to the court, Agence France-Presse reported.
</P>
<P>
The 12 judges of the court gave the verdict at 01:20 after
three-hour-and-50-minute deliberations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Carlos, 48 and of Venezuelan nationality, was condemned in
absentia to life imprisonment in 1992 by the same Paris court for
the murder of two French secret agents and their informer in the
Latin district of Paris on June 27, 1975.
</P>
<P>
He, who was abducted by French secret agents from Sudan in
1994, was also held responsible for the death of some 20 people in
terrorist attacks in the 1970s and 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
