vegetables before Christmas have nearly doubled due to supply
shortage caused by floods which have brought extensive damages to
roads and railways.
</P>
<P>
Several people told The Guardian newspaper in the downtown
areas of Dar es Salaam that they have to sneak out their offices
in order to get the merchandise before the eve of the Christmas
today, which is the most hectic day for shoppers.
</P>
<P>
Buka Kibona, acting Dar es Salaam Regional Police Commander,
has warned those who intend to cause trouble during the festival
to go to bed as early as possible in the evening, otherwise they
will be invited to police "guest house" which has neither beds
nor blankets. 
