Foreign Minister Qian Qichen left here this morning for Cairo,
Egypt to continue his Middle East tour.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day official visit to Israel, Qian met
President Ezer Weizman, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and had
talks with his counterpart David Levy on bilateral relations and
ways to push forward the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He told the Israeli leaders that China is very much concerned
about the impasse of the peace process and urged the Israeli
government to abide by the related U.N. resolutions and
land-for-peace principle agreed by all sides.
</P>
