<HEADLINE> Scenic Wuyi Mountains Benefit City Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Nanping City, where the scenic
Wuyi Mountains are located, is expected to earn 640 million yuan
(77.108 million US dollars) from tourism this year, up 72.5
percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
The city in northern Fujian Province is expected to receive
105,000 overseas tourists who will spend an estimated 11.55
million US dollars in Nanping this year, an increase of 43.8
percent and 58.2 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
New highways, the new Wuyishan Airport and a railway leading to
the Wuyi Mountains this year have helped propel the city's
tourism industry, said Mayor Li Chuan.
</P>
<P>
Seeing the bright prospects for tourism, the city has already
designated tourism as a pillar industry and will concentrate
efforts on improving travel routes leading to the Wuyi Mountains.
</P>
<P>
As part of the effort, a Hongkong investor recently opened a
tourism entertainment company which has decided to inject over 200
million yuan in the first phase of development in the scenic
Jiufeng Mountains and the Guyuezhou Island around the Yanping
Lake, which is the largest man-made lake in Fujian. 
</P>
