<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Receive ADB Loan for Urban Health Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive 40
million U.S. dollars in loan from the Asian Development Bank (ADB)
for an urban health project in the country's four major cities,
local press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed in Manila, the Philippines, between
Dhaka and the ADB Tuesday, the project will finance 15 partnership
agreements for providing health services such as immunization
support, family planning and parental health care in Dhaka,
Khulna, Chittagong and Rajshahi.
</P>
<P>
The project will also address diseases such measles,
tuberculosis, polio and sexually-transmitted diseases.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some 90 fully-equipped health centers will be set
up near urban slums.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan will carry an amortization period of 40 years,
including a grace period of 10 years.  
</P>
