<HEADLINE> Underground Boating Cave Attracts Tourists, Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- More and more tourists and
investors are flocking to the scenic Fengyu Cave in the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, believed to be the largest karst cave in
the world.
</P>
<P>
Lying 104 kilometers from the scenic city of Guilin City,
Fengyu Cave has a karst cave of 25,500 square meters, and a
3.3-km-long underground river, which is believed to be the longest
boating cave river in the world.
</P>
<P>
Since it opened to tourists in September of 1994, the
attraction has already received 1.3 million tourists.
</P>
<P>
While Chinese and overseas investored have already spent over
28 million yuan (3.37 million US dollars) in the development of
the cave and other tourist facilities, the Lipu County where the
cave is located has called for more financing for the construction
of a projected horse racing course, a cableway, and music
fountains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
