<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Confirms Stopping Russian Aid Plane to Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Iran today confirmed it has
stopped a Russian aid plane carrying a Russian team of parliament
members (MPs) and businessmen to Iraq by defying the U.N.
sanctions on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Russian aircraft, which was scheduled to land in Iraq
today, was currently held up with a delegation of 20 people at
Iran's western city of Kermanshah near Iraqi border.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Foreign Ministry said in an announcement last night
the Russian Tupolev-204 plane was carrying medicine for Iraqi
children.
</P>
<P>
Iran has asked for U.N. authorization to send the shipment of
Russian humanitarian aid to Iraq though a land route and Iranian
officials in Kermanshah were prepared to do so.
</P>
<P>
"Sending the cargo through air would only be possible through
special U.N. authorization," the source noted, adding that "it is
natural that Iran continues to abide by U.N. sanctions regulations
on Iraq."
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Iran News quoted an unnamed "analyst" as saying
that "Iran attaches paramount importance to international laws and
norms and was unable to let the Russian plane fly into Iraq
without authorization" from the U.N..
</P>
<P>
"We all know that the United Nations has imposed sanctions on
Iraq because of Baghdad's invasion of its tiny neighbor Kuwait in
1990, on the basis of U.N. sanctions, no plane can fly into Iraq
except those of U.N. carrying food and medicine," he said.
</P>
<P>
Iran rejected Baghdad's accusation that it was preventing the
Russian aircraft to fly to Iraq, saying that Baghdad "is
distorting the facts on Iran."
</P>
<P>
A Russia official was quoted as saying that negotiations were
in progress with the Iranian authorities over the issue, hoping a
solution to be found in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said this issue would be solved soon since
"it is a humanitarian flight and not commercial and it does not
break the international embargo."
</P>
<P>
According to the Iraqi side, the flight of Russian Tupolev-204
was an initiative of Russian ultra-nationalist MP Vladimir
Zhirinovsky who heads the Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) and has
strongly criticized the sanctions imposed on Iraq following its
1990 invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The plane was chartered by the LDP and carrying 20 LDP
representatives in the State Duma (lower house of the parliament)
and specialists along with aid supplies.
</P>
<P>
It was attempting to sidestep the U.N. ban on flights to and
from Iraq by asking for approval from Azerbaijan and Iran through
which it would pass instead of U.N. authorization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971224.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lithuania to Deport 103 Sri Lankan Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Lithuanian government will
on Thursday deport 103 Sri Lankans who were not holding proper
travel documents, an official in the Sri Lankan Foreign Ministry
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The deportees will arrive on a special flight chartered by the
Lithuanian government, Director Councilor B.G.R. Uyangoda of the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Altogether there are 200 illegal Sri Lankan immigrants
apprehended in Lithuania. The remaining 97 will be deported later,
the official added.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankans are believed to have planned to go to
Scandinavian nations via Lithuania, which is held by most illegal
immigrants as a gateway to their final destination.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania had deported 11 Afghans, 56 Pakistanis and 100
Bangladeshis this month. All were illegal immigrants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
