<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Enter Shanghai Bus Service Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- For the first time Shanghai
has permitted foreign companies to invest in its public transport
sector, with a joint Shanghai-Singapore bus venture established
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-Singapore Bus Corporation Ltd., with a registered
capital of 100 million yuan, will run 15 bus lines in the urban
area. The lines have been leased to the company for 25 years, and so
have been the 40 stations and offices along the lines.
</P>
<P>
The company has decided to speed up the replacement of old
buses with new ones, so that new buses will account for more than
60 percent of the total within three years.
</P>
<P>
This practice has changed the city's single state ownership in
the public transport sector, experts say, and has provided a new
approach to the growth of the state-owned bus companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
