<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Facing New Adjustment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- China has to readjust its
economic structure to maintain healthy development, a high
ranking official from the State Planning Commission has said.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Yanpei, vice-minister in charge of the commission, said in
an article carried by today's People's Daily that the country has
in the last years raised its overall economic strength mainly by
increasing investment and building new projects.
</P>
<P>
During the forthcoming economic restructuring, attention will
be paid on improving economic quality and increasing efficiency,
he said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has made great achievements in economic
restructuring by developing backbone industries and creating new
economic driving force, but the progress is not satisfactory, he
added.
</P>
<P>
To speed up the progress, he called for efforts on developing
new industries and high-tech industries, such as the electronic
information industry.
</P>
<P>
According to him, electronic firms should be encouraged to set
up large conglomerates which are more competent on the
international market.
</P>
<P>
Housing construction for urban and rural residents should be
accelerated and the ongoing housing reform be further carried out,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The equipment of the State-owned enterprises should be
modernized to bring the overall economy to a new high level, added
Zeng.
</P>
<P>
The official also called on enlarging rural market for
household electrical appliances and manufacturing more equipment
for the industrialization of agriculture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
