<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Senate Passes 1998 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Italian Senate approved the
1998 budget and signed it into law today.
</P>
<P>
The government presented a package of 25 trillion liras
(14.5 billion dollars) in spending cuts and new taxes.
</P>
<P>
The measures are aimed at cutting Italy's deficit-to-GDP ration
to 2.8 percent next year from this year's target of 3 percent. The
figure is a requirement for European Monetary Union.
</P>
<P>
The government expects the spending measure to give Italy the
final push it needs to enter the European single currency among
the first group of nations on January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The budget was approved by the House on December 19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
