<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Lower at Midday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong shares lost 25.66
points, or 0.25 percent, to finish at 10,342.44 at Wednesday's
mid-day break.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index opened lower, dropping 117.31
points, or 1.13 percent, to hit 10,250.79 in the first several
minutes of trading.
</P>
<P>
The index gained 195.63 points, or 1.92 percent, to close at
10,368.10 on Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
