had made great contributions to the normalization and development
of the relations between Hungary and Romania.
</P>
<P>
Romania has achieved great successes in foreign affairs under
Severin's leadership, and the Hungary-Romania ties have been
advancing rapidly to benefit both countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman wished broad prospects for the future bilateral
ties to serve not only Romania's participation in the European
integration process but also the two countries' interests.
</P>
<P>
Severin resigned on Tuesday over his allegations made in
September that several political leaders and newspaper editors in
his country were spies for foreign intelligence services.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian Supreme Defense Council said "no elements were
found" to support his charges. President Emil Constantinescu, who
heads the council, said the accusations were "an error" and
suggested Severin should quit.
</P>
<P>
Premier Victor Ciorbea accepted the resignation, the state news
agency Rompres reported. 
