<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Thai senate speaker Meechai
Ruchuphan Tuesday denounced speculators for cashing in on the
country's economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
When people of all walks of life were making sacrifices for the
sake of the nation, speculators and their kind profited from the
crisis, Meechai was quoted by local newspapers as saying.
</P>
<P>
The speaker made the comment at a time when the Thai government
is cutting salaries or allowances for civil servants and state
enterprise employees, including senior officials and parliament
members, while some monks and public and private organizations are
launching a Thais-help-Thais fund to help the country pay off
debts.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the cut in senators' salaries, Meechai said that
although the cut contributes a little to the nation, it may give a
moral support to the government.
</P>
<P>
He threw his support for the government to crack down currency
and gold speculators, while calling on all Thais to curse them.
</P>
