<HEADLINE> Indonesia May Become Southeast Asia's Biggest Exporter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia may become Southeast
Asia's biggest exporter of electronic products in 2006, a
government official said.
</P>
<P>
"The target could be achieved, however, if by 2006 Indonesia is
able to export at least 40 billion US dollars worth of such
products," Electronics Industry Director at the Directorate
General of Multifarious Industry Ardiansyah Parman said Tuesday in
Medan, North Sumatra, according to reports reaching here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ardiansyah said Indonesia's electronic exports in 2000 are
projected to earn 10 billion dollars and will grow in volume and
value by an average of 25 percent per year till 2006.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the growth rate may be difficult to achieve
if Indonesia merely relies on the domestic electronic industry.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, it would be necessary for Indonesia to attract
foreign investment in the electronic industry subsector and team
up with world-class export-oriented electronic companies to
relocate their business to Indonesia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's electronic products earned 3.2 billion dollars in
foreign exchange in 1996, but still lower than that of several
other electronic producers in Southeast Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
