<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Makes Achievements in Banning on Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hainan Province
has scored marked achievements in the banning on drugs.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the January-July period show that public
security organs in the province crashed 294 cases of drug
trafficking and 805 cases of drug taking, up 14.4 percent and
57.2 percent over the same period of 1996 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 45 drug trafficking gangs were smashed, and over
6,300 grams of drugs were confiscated.
</P>
<P>
In the January-September period, local courts tried 184
drug-related cases, involving 296 people.
</P>
<P>
From January to July this year, 2,614 drug addicts were forced
to stop using drugs.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the province also has stressed publicizing knowledge
of the banning on drugs and related education on youngsters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
