<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Stresses Importance of EU Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Fully developing relations
with the European Union (EU) is a long-term strategic principle
for the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, its Foreign Minister,
Milan Milutionvic, said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Milutionvic made the remarks after meeting with visiting
Portugal Foreign Minister Zzaim Gama.
</P>
<P>
He said Portugal expressed its understanding and support for
Yugoslavia's goal in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The talks centered on bilateral ties, especially economic
cooperation, and hoped a new height in the relationship could be
achieved, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Gama said the two countries' diplomatic relations will be
upgraded to ambassadorial level next year.
</P>
<P>
Portugal and Yugoslavia, he said, closely cooperated in the
EU's favorable trading policy as it applied to Yugoslavia and the
latter's return soon to the Organization of Security and
Cooperation of Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
Gama also met Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic and Prime
Minister Radoje Kontic Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
His two-day visit is the first high-level official visit to
Yugoslavia by Portugal in more than a decade. 
