<HEADLINE> First Winter Camp for Overweight Children to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Twelve-year-old girl Qian Xi,
weighing over 84.5 kg, came to the Tianjin Children's Hospital
today to apply for the city's first winter camp for obese children.
</P>
<P>
The five-day camp, sponsored by the Tianjin Municipal Women's
Federation, will be held in the coming winter vacation. More than
100 obese children will receive the instructions on diet and
physical exercises from experts.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yao, director of the Tianjin Children's Hospital, said
that they have developed some effective methods to rapidly reduce
the weight of the children through proper diet and physical
exercises.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, we want the children to cultivate healthy habits,
which will have a long-term effect on their future life," said
Wang.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of the living conditions, more and more
Chinese children are as fat as Qian Xi. This can be attributed to
excessive eating and drinking and lack of physical exercises.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that Chinese children intake too much fat and
sugar, and sit in front of the TV all day long while having little
physical exercises.
</P>
<P>
The number of the obese children aged between seven and
fourteen in Tianjin has exceeded 3,000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
