<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share-Holding Enterprises Contributing to Shanghai's Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Shareholding enterprises have
become a major contributor to the industrial production of
Shanghai, China's largest metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, Shanghai has turned 55 industrial
enterprises into shareholding ones, according to the city's
Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
By the end of October, the 55 enterprises had 37.2 billion yuan
in sales, accounting for 10.3 percent of the city's total. And
their combined assets amounted to 95.6 billion yuan, or 14 percent
of the total.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the investment returns and other profits by the
shareholding companies have made up nearly a quarter of the city's
total profits of the industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 46 of the 55 enterprises were established
in the 1992-93 period. They have a total investment of more than
18 billion yuan, 15 billion of which have been spent expanding the
city's industrial capacity.
</P>
<P>
This year, Shanghai has begun to reorganize the assets of
several large industrial enterprises, and turned some of them into
shareholding companies.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
