<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Encourages Rapid Growth of Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi will
step up its efforts to promote local private enterprises in the
coming years.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government plans to raise the proportion of
private industrial output value to 15 percent of the province's
total, and increase the number of private industrial and
commercial enterprises to 30,000 by the end of the century,
according to Yang Yongshan, an official with Shaanxi Provincial
Economic Commission.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also intends to develop large private
enterprises to further promote economic development in Shaanxi,
Yang said.
</P>
<P>
To speed the process along, local officials are being asked to
refrain from discriminating against private enterprises and
individual industrial and commercial households, as has been done
in the past, and to try harder to provide better service to them,
he added.
</P>
<P>
In the past decade, the inland province witnessed great
progress in the development of its private economy. By the end of
1996, Shaanxi had 17,800 private enterprises employing 1.45
million workers, and the industrial output value of these
enterprises had reached 10.8 percent of the province's total.
</P>
</TEXT>
