<HEADLINE> Beijing Has More Telephone Subscribers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of telephone
subscribers in the urban areas of Beijing has increased by
550,000 and that for mobile phones by 300,000 this year.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the total number of telephone subscribers in the
city has reached 2.5 million and that of mobile phone subscribers
600,000. The city's telephone coverage rate stands at 38 percent,
and the figure for urban areas is 55 percent.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1997, Beijing this year has invested 5
billion yuan in building telecom infrastructure facilities,
including over 1,600 kilometers of optical fibre, which brings the
total length of the city's optical fibre to over 6,200 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Various telephone switchboards with a combined capacity of 1.1
million lines were put into operation, bringing the
combined capacity of local telephone switchboards to 3.8 million
lines and the capacity of mobile phone switchboards to 760,000
lines.
</P>
<P>
The city has also made marked progress in developing Internet
subscribers and E-mail services. 
