<HEADLINE> Southwest China's County Raises Millions of Yuan To Build Roads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Cangwu County in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region raised 11.53 million yuan this
year to build 15 roads, totally 130 kilometers in length.
</P>
<P>
About over 70 percent of the funds were raised from
villagers. Rest of the funds are allocations from the state and
the county government.
</P>
<P>
The county government has decided that since this year Cangwu
will complete 100 kilometers of rural roads annually, and by the
year 2000, 85 percent of the villages in the county will be linked
by roads.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the county communications bureau show that by
the end of November, 158 villages in Cangwu had been linked by
roads, accounting for 65 percent of the total villages in the
county. 
