<HEADLINE> Shaolin Martial Arts to Widely Spread With Help of Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The famous Shaolin martial arts,
Buddhism and special medical therapies will be spread more widely
in the world as the Shaolin Monastery has connected with
the Internet recently.
</P>
<P>
Located near Zhengzhou, capital of central China's Henan
province, the Shaolin Monastery is one of the most well-known
temples in China.
</P>
<P>
Shi Yongxin, Abbot of the monastery, said through the Internet,
Chinese and foreign readers can learn the history and culture of
the Shaolin Monastry through photos, materials and data.
</P>
<P>
He added that they can learn how the monks sit in meditation
and how they practice their boxing.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the martial arts include boxing, Aigong,
capture methods and military strategy and tactics.
</P>
<P>
The abbot added that the medical therapies include acupuncture
and moxibustion and massage.
</P>
<P>
Shi said since China's open-up drive in the late 1970s, his
monastery receives each day over 10,000 visitors or people who came
to learn the Shaolin martial arts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
