during which period the Lakers have posted an 11-6 record. The
Lakers went 4-1 on a recent road trip which concluded with a 94-83
win Monday over the Houston Rockets.
</P>
<P>
After four seasons with the Orlando Magic, O'Neal signed a
seven-year, 121 million U.S. dollars free-agent deal with the
Lakers in the summer of 1996. He averaged 26.2 points and 12.6
rebounds in 51 games last season, sitting out 31 games with
various ailments, including ligament damage in his left knee.
