<HEADLINE> Alenichev Named Russia's 1997 Top Player </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Dmitry Alenichev of Russian
champions Spartak Moscow was named the country's top player of
1997 by the Russian Football Union on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The attacking midfielder, who celebrated his 25th birthday on
Saturday, beat Rotor Volgograd's Oleg Veretennikov and Torpedo
Moscow's Dmitry Khokhlov to win the honour.
</P>
<P>
Alenichev earned the award after playing a key role in Russia's
World Cup campaign and leading Spartak to their fifth league title.
</P>
<P>
Benfica goalkeeper Sergei Ovchinnikov, who joined the Portugese
club from Lokomotiv Moscow earlier this year, won the trophy for
the best foreign-based player, edging out defender Viktor Onopko,
who plays for Oviedo of Spain and striker Sergei Yuran of
Germany's Bochum.
</P>
<P>
Alenichev was also the first choice of the Russian premier
division coaches and the national team coaching staff for the Most
Valuable Player award. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
