<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Plane Crash in Illinois </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A single-engine plane
crashed in rural northern Illinois Monday night, killing all four
people aboard, reports from Hampshire said today.
</P>
<P>
The Piper Saratoga went down into a muddy farm near Interstate
90 and Illinois Route 20 and near Hampshire.
</P>
<P>
Police found the wreckage this morning and removed the four
people, two men and two women, from the wreckage. Two were in the
aircraft and the other two were out in the field.
</P>
<P>
The four-seat aircraft crashed nose first skidding across the
field and may have flipped over.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was not immediately known. The Federal
Aviation Administration and the National Transportation Safety
Board were investigating. 
</P>
