<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Plunge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street fell
sharply during the last trading hour Tuesday following another
panicky selloff in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average sank 127.54 points to
7,691.77, after holding steady for most of the session.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by an 8-to-7 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 513.93 million shares as
against 530.09 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 14.59 to 939.11, and
the NYSE composite index fell 5.63 to 494.85.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 22.15 to 1,509.91, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 2.55 to 660.52.
</P>
<P>
Broad-market indicators were also hit hard late in the session.
</P>
<P>
U.S. investors may have drawn some confidence from European
markets, which shrugged off the turmoil in South Korea, where
stocks plunged a record 7.5 percent. 
</P>
