<HEADLINE> French PM Appeals for Relaunching of Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin appealed this evening for the relaunching of the peace
process between Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony held at the prime minister's office building,
Hotel Matignon, to start the celebrations in France of the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the state of Israel, Jospin said
that Israel should follow the way opened in Madrid and Oslo.
</P>
<P>
He called on Israel to "resolutely relaunch the negotiations
with Yasser Arafat on the future of the (Israeli) occupied
territories."
</P>
<P>
He said that the decision made 50 years ago by the United
Nations to create simultaneously two states -- one Jewish and one
Arab -- signified that a state could not last long if it was not
accepted by its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
In his response to Jospin, Israeli ambassador to France Avi
Pazner said that Israel would do its best not to leave France
"disappointed".
</P>
<P>
"The deepest hope of Israel is to continue this peace process,"
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
