<HEADLINE> Former French FM Makes Secret Mission to Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Former French foreign minister
Claude Cheysson has lately made a secret mission to Algeria during
which he met with Algerian President Liamine Zeroual.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the LCI cable television channel,
Cheysson, who was foreign minister under former president Francois
Mitterrand, said that the "highest authorities (of France) are
very interested in the conclusions that I would draw from this
trip."
</P>
<P>
But Cheysson refused to reveal the content of his talks with
President Zeroual.
</P>
<P>
He blamed the on-going violence in Algeria mainly on religious
fanaticism, which he said "could not but be eradicated."
</P>
<P>
But he also accused organized crimes and "some elements of the
power" of participating in the violence, which has claimed at
least 60,000 lives over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Relations with Algeria are the most paradoxical issue in the
foreign policy of France, which was the former colonial power of
the North African nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
